Hi Brad,
Thanks! I was eyeing that facet of this problem and noticed an interesting anomaly in how the HDF5 files are being interpreted by the hdf5_handler.
In the DDS response for one of the HDF5 files:
http://test.opendap.org/opendap/viirs/VNP13A1.A2018145.h10v04.001.2018161235134.h5.dds
there are these variables:
String ArchiveMetadata_0;
String CoreMetadata_0;
String StructMetadata_0;
Which I believe are being used as an organizational convention for organizing the metadata.
What I noticed is that in the metadata (DAS) response for the same file:
http://test.opendap.org/opendap/viirs/VNP13A1.A2018145.h10v04.001.2018161235134.h5.das
The variables have different names:
ArchiveMetadata {
}
CoreMetadata {
}
StructMetadata {
}
I am pretty sure that this is never supposed to happen.
And I wonder if the NcML code the handles the aggregation could be stumbling over this.
Sincerely,
Nathan
